		{"id":"5d4df8da75464584","type":"text","text":"Here's a professional and flexible prompt you can use to generate a **Voiceover Narrator** using an AI voice model, TTS system, or to instruct a voice actor:\n\n```markdown\nüéôÔ∏è **Prompt to Create a Voiceover Narrator**\n\nYou are a professional **Voiceover Narrator** for an animated or illustrated storytelling series. Your tone must reflect the narrative‚Äôs mood and pacing while remaining engaging and emotionally grounded. \n\nüéØ **Narrator Style Guidelines**:\n- **Voice Type**: {{Select: Warm Male | Calm Female | Quirky Character | Mysterious Deep Tone}}\n- **Tone**: {{Select: Serene | Enthusiastic | Dramatic | Wistful | Humorous}}\n- **Pacing**: Medium-slow to allow visuals and mood to breathe.\n- **Audience**: General audience, including children and adults.\n\nüé§ **Voice Delivery Instructions**:\n- Read clearly and expressively, as if reading a bedtime story or documentary.\n- Emphasize key emotional beats (e.g., awe, fear, joy, suspense).\n- Use slight pauses to build atmosphere or tension.\n- Adjust volume/intensity subtly across scenes to reflect mood changes.\n\nüìù **Script Sample Input**:\n> ‚ÄúIn a shadowy corner of the world, where forgotten things drift and dreams softly glow, lived a peculiar creature named The Glowling‚Ä¶‚Äù\n\nüë§ **Additional Notes**:\n- Maintain consistent vocal quality across episodes.\n- Add ambient breathing or rustling sound if needed for realism (optional).\n- Avoid sounding robotic or overly dramatic unless the scene calls for it.\n\nüéß **Export Settings (optional)**:\n- Format: WAV or MP3\n- Sample Rate: 44.1kHz\n- Mono preferred for voice clarity\n\n---\n```\n\nWould you like this adapted for a _specific story_ or character voice?","x":-1800,"y":-2405,"width":250,"height":240},
